      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FUGITIVE NZ (5) has not raced for three-and-a-half months since finishing down the track the NSW Derby but had some good form prior including a win at this venue in his Australian debut along with a placing at Listed level at Melton. Looks forward enough for the return after a minor placing in a recent trial. Top chance. OSHLEY (1) took on a good field last time so is suited dropping in grade. Can be much more competitive at this level with the aid of the inside draw. SHORELINE DREAM (10) is a newcomer to the Seaton Grima yard from SA. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw but he has won two of three fresh attempts. EYE CAN EAR AMOUR (8) came from this barrier for a well-deserved last-start win at this circuit and distance to follow back-to-back placings. Go well again.",
